Preconditions:
- The input integer `n` must be greater than or equal to - The length of the input 2D integer array `roads` must be greater than or equal to - Each element `roads[i]` in the `roads` array must be an array of length - The values of `a_i` and `b_i` in each `roads[i]` array must be between 0 and `n - 1`.
- The values of `a_i` and `b_i` in each `roads[i]` array must be different.
- There should be no duplicate roads.

Postconditions:
- The method should return a long integer representing the maximum total importance of all roads.
- The assigned values to each city should be integers from 1 to `n`.
- Each value can only be used once.
- The importance of a road is defined as the sum of the values of the two cities it connects.